    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 3 Exponential (weighted) average\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Exponential (weighted) average means that we want to put more weight on the prices of the most recent days and less weight on the old prices. The weights in our case decrease exponentially.\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* $EMA_N = \\\\dfrac{p_0 + (1-\\\\alpha)p_1 + (1-\\\\alpha)^2p_2 + ... + (1-\\\\alpha)^{n} p_{n}}{1 + (1-\\\\alpha) + (1-\\\\alpha)^2 + ... + (1-\\\\alpha)^{n}}$\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* $p_i$ is the stock price form the $i$-th day, $p_0$ is today’s price and $p_n$ - the price from $n$ days ago\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* $\\\\alpha = \\\\dfrac{2}{n+1}$\\n\",\n",
    "    \"* $n+1$ -  number of prices (days) taken into account\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Tasks: \\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4) Compute the exponential average value of the data for *n=9*. \\n\",\n",
    "    \"5) Define *exp_avr()* function, which computes exponential average for specified data and *n*\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-04-17T11:50:44.498328600Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-04-17T11:50:44.461614Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"def exp_avr(data, n): #making new f\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    alpha = 2 / (n+1)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    numerator = 0\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    denominator = 0\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    for i in range(n+1):\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        weight = (1 - alpha)**i #weight for certain day\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        numerator += weight * data[i] #data by day times weight\\n\",\n",
    "    \"        denominator += weight\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    return numerator / denominator\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": 12\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {\n",
    "    \"ExecuteTime\": {\n",
    "     \"end_time\": \"2026-04-17T11:50:46.994420700Z\",\n",
    "     \"start_time\": \"2026-04-17T11:50:46.926012700Z\"\n",
    "    }\n",
    "   },\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# your code\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"data_calc = data_10_days[::-1] #switching\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"result_9 = exp_avr(data_calc, 9)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"result for 9 is {result_9:.4f}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ],\n",
